cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.RO 

This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it presents a synthetic dataset to evaluate video prediction networks. It may also belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category as it proposes the use of a performance metric to improve experimental interpretability. Additionally, it could be classified under Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) as it deals with the representation learning of video prediction models. Neural Networks (cs.NE) and Robotics (cs.RO) are also possible sub-categories as they are related to the study of video prediction networks.
